            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Bulbasaur", 0.7, 6.9, "Seed", "Overgrow", "Grass & Poison", 1, "Ivysaur", "At the beginning of its life, it feeds on the nutrients stored in the seed on its back. This allows it to grow", 1, "Classified as a Grass- and Poison-type Pokémon, Bulbasaur is one of three starter Pokémon players are able to select at the game's beginning. It is a quadrupedal green creature resembling a dinosaur, with a large plant bulb on its back. Bulbasaur is a central character in the Pokémon anime, being one of Ash Ketchum's main Pokémon for the first season, with a different one later obtained by supporting character May. It is featured in various manga and is owned by protagonist Red in Pokémon Adventures.\r\n\r\nBulbasaur is generally considered one of the most popular and widely liked Pokémon, having ranked highly in official popularity polls.[5] Series producer Junichi Masuda has also specifically mentioned Bulbasaur as one of his favorite Pokémon. Its role in the anime has been suggested to have played a factor into its popularity."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Ivysaur", 1.0, 13.0, "Seed", "Overgrow", "Grass & Poison", 1, "Venusaur", "The more it is exposed to the sun, the more energy it stores, which allows the bud on its back to develop.", 2, "Ivysaur are able to naturally learn the powerful Grass-type attack Solar Beam, a move whose execution time depends largely upon the weather; it takes an excruciatingly long amount of time to perform this attack in hail, rain, or a sandstorm, but nearly no time at all in bright sunlight. Luckily, the latter is ​most common in the habitats of these Pokémon, as it is vital that the bulbs on their backs receive ample sunlight so that they can photosynthesize and develop. As the bulbs grow larger and these Ivysaur become more powerful, they must spend increasing amounts of time in the sun in order to foster their growth. When Ivysaur are preparing to evolve into Venusaur, they will spend more time sunbathing and their bulbs will begin emanating a sweet, pleasant aroma."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Venusaur", 2.0, 100.0, "Seed", "Overgrow", "Grass & Poison", 1, "None", "This Pokémon is capable of transforming sunlight into energy. It is therefore even stronger in summer.", 3, "Venusaur absorbs sunlight to gain energy and to feed its flower, located on its back. After gaining a certain amount of sunlight, the flower will release a sweet aroma said to soothe the emotions of people. Additionally, after a rainy day, the smell of the flower's aroma grows stronger, attracting other Pokémon.\r\n\r\nThe power of Gigantamaxing has made Venusaur's flower bloom so large that it covers the Pokémon's body. The flower's petals are extremely thick and springy enough to repel halfhearted attacks. During battle, the Pokémon uses these petals as a shield and swings its two thick vines around to attack its target.\r\n\r\nThe flower on the Pokémon's back spews so much pollen that it resembles a volcanic eruption. Inhaling the pollen can cause uncontrollable sneezing, and breathing in too much of it can even cause fainting. However, the pollen also stimulates plant growth. Places where the pollen falls are said to grow thick with large plants."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Charmander", 0.6, 8.5, "Lizard", "Brasier", "Fire", 1, "Charmeleon", "The flame at the end of its tail represents its vitality. When it is not at its best, it weakens.", 4, "Charmander is easily the most mild-mannered and well-behaved of its evolution line. Its feelings and emotions can be read by the flame on the tip of its tail. It flares up in a fury when Charmander is angry. The flame will flicker and grow small and dim if Charmander is sick or hurt. If it growls, that means it's angry or is about to attack.\r\n\r\nCharmander, however, doesn't do well with impatient people. It doesn't appreciate being rushed, and most of the time, will not allow it. It is a sweet Pokémon, but is feisty nonetheless. Charmander doesn't enjoy accepting favors, because it feels it owes something in return. It is extremely loyal to its loved ones, and knows a good thing when it sees it. It will treat those in its life accordingly.\r\n\r\nCharmander is rarely found in the wild since it's a first partner Pokémon. Sometimes they gather in extremely hot areas such as active volcanoes or in craggy mountains and in caves along the coast of the Sevii Islands."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Charmeleon", 1.1, 19.0, "Flamme", "Brasier", "Fire", 1, "Charizard", "By waving its flaming tail, it can exponentially raise the ambient temperature and thus torment its opponents.", 5, "Charmeleon, like its other evolutionary forms, can naturally breathe fire. Its powers, though, are much greater than Charmander's, but not as great as Charizard's.\r\n\r\nCharmeleon is also much more aggressive than Charmander. It is believed to have a vicious nature and will constantly seek out opponents. Strong opponents excite this Pokémon, causing it to spout bluish-white flames that torch its surroundings. It is a very ruthless, pitiless and zealous fighter often using its claws. However, it will relax once it has won.\r\n\r\nIn their fervor, their tails often begin to burn a bluish-white; at night, they can light up mountainsides like stars if groups of them are present. Enraged Charmeleon often take out their anger on their surroundings, incinerating anything flammable around them with unrestrained Flamethrowers.\r\n\r\nThis stage is often likened to a human’s teenage years--moody and reckless. Charmander and Charizard, can be found in hot, rocky mountainous areas."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Charizard", 1.7, 90.5, "Flamme", "Brasier", "Fire & Flying", 1, "None", "When he gets really angry, the flame at the end of his tail turns blue.", 6, "Charizard are noble and will not turn the full power of their flame on opponents significantly weaker than themselves. They are also known to be very eager to battle. Charizard seeks out stronger foes and only breathes fire during battles with worthy opponents. The fiery breath is so hot that it can turn any material to slag. They can be very dangerous and aggressive if provoked, but like its previous evolutions, Charizard is generally friendly and loyal to a skilled Trainer. Charizard only ignores its Trainer if it feels that they do not care about it.\r\n\r\nIn the anime, only a weak or poorly trained Charizard actively shows off its power, as said by Liza in \"Charizard's Burning Ambitions\". In rare cases, Charizard will evolve from a less civilized Charmeleon and keep an un-preferable behavior. In any such cases, training will work but will be difficult."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Squirtle", 0.5, 9.0, "Tiny Turtle", "Torrent", "Water", 1, "Wartortle", "After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It sprays a potent foam from its mouth.", 7, "Squirtle's shell is not merely used for protection. The shell's rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, allowing this Pokémon to swim at high speeds."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Wartortle", 1.0, 22.5, "Turtle", "Torrent", "Water", 1, "Blastoise", "Its tail is large and covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. It is very popular among collectors.", 8, "It is said that Wartortle live for 10,000 years. Its furry tail is a symbol of longevity, and it is often used as a symbol of wisdom by the elderly."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Blastoise", 1.6, 85.5, "Shellfish", "Torrent", "Water", 1, "None", "The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.", 9, "Blastoise has powerful water cannons that extend from its shell. They are made of steel and can be withdrawn. The Pokémon fires pressurized water bullets from them to take down even the toughest opponents."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Caterpie", 0.3, 2.9, "Worm", "Shield Dust", "Bug", 1, "Metapod", "For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.", 10, "Its feet have suction cups that allow it to climb any surface, including glass. It sheds its skin many times, growing rapidly each time before it is ready to form a cocoon."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Metapod", 0.7, 9.9, "Cocoon", "Shed Skin", "Bug", 1, "Butterfree", "A steel-hard shell protects its soft, tender body. It endures attacks while awaiting evolution.", 11, "This Pokémon is completely vulnerable to attack while its shell is hardening. It remains motionless to avoid detection, preparing for its evolution into Butterfree."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Butterfree", 1.1, 32.0, "Butterfly", "Compound Eyes", "Bug & Flying", 1, "None", "It loves the honey of flowers and can locate patches of flowers with honey even at night.", 12, "Its wings are covered in fine, poisonous dust. If you find a Butterfree in the forest, it likely has a favorite flower whose nectar it drinks every day."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Weedle", 0.3, 3.2, "Hairy Bug", "Shield Dust", "Bug & Poison", 1, "Kakuna", "Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.", 13, "It eats its weight in leaves every day. It is small but its venomous stinger makes it a dangerous foe. The barb on its head secretes a strong poison."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Kakuna", 0.6, 10.0, "Cocoon", "Shed Skin", "Bug & Poison", 1, "Beedrill", "Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.", 14, "While it awaits evolution, it mainly stays still. If it is threatened, it can only raise its stinger to fend off attackers."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Beedrill", 1.0, 29.5, "Poison Bee", "Swarm", "Bug & Poison", 1, "None", "It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to stab enemies repeatedly.", 15, "Beedrill is extremely territorial. Anyone who approaches its nest will be met with a relentless assault by the entire swarm."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Pidgey", 0.3, 1.8, "Tiny Bird", "Keen Eye", "Normal & Flying", 1, "Pidgeotto", "It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.", 16, "Pidgey has an excellent sense of direction. It is capable of unerringly returning to its nest, no matter how far away it may be separated from its familiar surroundings."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Pidgeotto", 1.1, 30.0, "Bird", "Keen Eye", "Normal & Flying", 1, "Pidgeot", "This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its territory in search of prey.", 17, "Pidgeotto claims a large area as its territory. It flies around patrolling its territory and uses its sharp talons to snatch prey like Exeggcute from the ground."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Pidgeot", 1.5, 39.5, "Bird", "Keen Eye", "Normal & Flying", 1, "None", "When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.", 18, "This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons. It can spread its beautiful glossy wings to intimidate foes."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Rattata", 0.3, 3.5, "Mouse", "Run Away", "Normal", 1, "Raticate", "It eats anything. It will forage for food all night, even invading human settlements.", 19, "Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while sleeping, its ears twitch, listening for any sound of danger. It will attack anything with a simple bite."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Raticate", 0.7, 18.5, "Mouse", "Run Away", "Normal", 1, "None", "Its hind legs are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.", 20, "Its whiskers are essential for maintaining balance. Its incisors are very strong and grow constantly, so it must gnaw on hard things to wear them down."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Spearow", 0.3, 2.0, "Tiny Bird", "Keen Eye", "Normal & Flying", 1, "Fearow", "Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.", 21, "It is very territorial and will loudly screech to intimidate intruders. Even Pidgey can be frightened off by its angry cry."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Fearow", 1.2, 38.0, "Beak", "Keen Eye", "Normal & Flying", 1, "None", "A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away instantly.", 22, "Fearow is recognized by its long neck and elongated beak. Its long neck is perfect for capturing prey on land or water. It can carry away small prey in an instant."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Ekans", 2.0, 6.9, "Snake", "Intimidate", "Poison", 1, "Arbok", "The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.", 23, "It moves silently and stealthily. It eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, by coiling itself around them and crushing them."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Arbok", 3.5, 65.0, "Cobra", "Intimidate", "Poison", 1, "None", "The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.", 24, "The pattern on its belly is used for intimidation. It has been proven that this pattern is different in each geographic region, leading to many different variations."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Pikachu", 0.4, 6.0, "Mouse", "Static", "Electric", 1, "Raichu", "When it is angry, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.", 25, "Pikachu stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When they are fully charged, it might sometimes be approached by other Pikachu who want to play."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Raichu", 0.8, 30.0, "Mouse", "Static", "Electric", 1, "None", "If the electric pouches in its cheeks become overcharged, it will discharge and may also start shaking.", 26, "It has the power to send out electricity of 100,000 volts. It can be dangerous if it becomes overcharged, so it discharges regularly through its tail into the ground."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Sandshrew", 0.6, 12.0, "Mouse", "Sand Veil", "Ground", 1, "Sandslash", "It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.", 27, "When it curls up in a ball, it can deflect any attack. It is covered with dry, hard skin that is so tough it can shrug off any simple attack."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Sandslash", 1.0, 29.5, "Mouse", "Sand Veil", "Ground", 1, "None", "It curls up in a ball, then rolls into its enemies. Its sharp spines can cause severe damage.", 28, "It is adept at attacking with its claws. When it rolls into a ball, its sharp spines can pierce the hands of any attacker. It prefers dry and sandy areas."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidoran♀", 0.4, 7.0, "Poison Pin", "Poison Point", "Poison", 1, "Nidorina", "Although small, its venomous barbs make this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.", 29, "Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidorina", 0.8, 20.0, "Poison Pin", "Poison Point", "Poison", 1, "Nidoqueen", "When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retreat. This is proof that it is relaxed.", 30, "Its friendly disposition toward people means it is often kept as a pet. However, its barves are still dangerous and secrete poison when it is nervous."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidoqueen", 1.3, 60.0, "Drill", "Poison Point", "Poison & Ground", 1, "None", "Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect its offspring with its own life.", 31, "Nidoqueen is adept at fighting with its thick, armored body. It uses its body to protect its nest and young from attackers."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidoran♂", 0.5, 9.0, "Poison Pin", "Poison Point", "Poison", 1, "Nidorino", "Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.", 32, "It is small but its horns contain a potent venom. It is always moving its large ears around, keeping alert for danger."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidorino", 0.9, 19.5, "Poison Pin", "Poison Point", "Poison", 1, "Nidoking", "Quick on its feet, it tears at enemies with its hard claws. It is aggressive and attacks with its horn.", 33, "Its horn is harder than diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Nidoking", 1.4, 62.0, "Drill", "Poison Point", "Poison & Ground", 1, "None", "It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn, as it contains venom.", 34, "Nidoking's thick tail packs tremendously destructive power. With one swing, it can topple a metal transmission tower. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Clefairy", 0.6, 7.5, "Fairy", "Cute Charm", "Fairy", 1, "Clefable", "It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.", 35, "Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this adorable Pokémon is rarely found."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Clefable", 1.3, 40.0, "Fairy", "Cute Charm", "Fairy", 1, "None", "A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.", 36, "Clefable moves by skipping lightly as if it were flying. Its bouncy step lets it walk even on water. It is known to take walks on lakes on quiet, moonlit nights."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Vulpix", 0.6, 9.9, "Fox", "Flash Fire", "Fire", 1, "Ninetales", "As it grows, its six tails grow more beautiful. When it is warm, they curl elegantly.", 37, "While young, it has six beautiful tails. When it evolves, it grows many more. It is weak to cold temperatures, so it lives in volcanic areas."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Ninetales", 1.1, 19.9, "Fox", "Flash Fire", "Fire", 1, "None", "It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.", 38, "It possesses an innate talent for creating illusions. It is said that it can curse anyone who mistreats it. Its nine tails are said to be imbued with power."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Jigglypuff", 0.5, 5.5, "Balloon", "Cute Charm", "Normal & Fairy", 1, "Wigglytuff", "When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysterious melody. That melody is actually a lullaby.", 39, "Jigglypuff can inflate itself like a balloon. When it sings, it breathes deeply, expanding and contracting. Its captivating song can put anyone to sleep."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Wigglytuff", 1.0, 12.0, "Balloon", "Cute Charm", "Normal & Fairy", 1, "None", "It has a very fine fur. It is careful not to let it become dirty, and it will hate anyone who tries to mess with it.", 40, "Its fur is extremely fine and silky. When it gets angry, it takes a deep breath and inflates itself to more than twice its size."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Zubat", 0.8, 7.5, "Bat", "Inner Focus", "Poison & Flying", 1, "Golbat", "It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, it flies around.", 41, "Zubat avoids sunlight because exposure to it causes its body to become unhealthy. During the day, it gathers with others and hangs from the ceilings of dark caves."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Golbat", 1.6, 55.0, "Bat", "Inner Focus", "Poison & Flying", 1, "None", "It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and suck blood.", 42, "It can drink more than 10 ounces of blood at once. If it drinks too much, it becomes heavy and can't fly safely."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Oddish", 0.5, 5.4, "Weed", "Chlorophyll", "Grass & Poison", 1, "Gloom", "If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.", 43, "During the day, Oddish buries itself in the ground to absorb nutrients. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become."));
            pokemons.Add(new Pokemon("Gloom", 0.8, 8.6, "Weed", "Chlorophyll", "Grass & Poison", 1, "Vileplume", "Its pistil exudes an incredibly foul odor. The horrid smell can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.", 44, "The smell from its nose drips and smells so terrible that it can cause fainting. It is so foul that even other Gloom can't stand it."));
